### Steps to reproduce


 `<el-table-column label="score" width="60" align="center">
            <template slot-scope="scope">
              <input class="input-line" v-number style="width:100%" type="text" v-model="scope.row.score" />
            </template>
          </el-table-column>
`

`  directives: {
    number: {
      inserted: function(el, binding, vnode) {
        el.oninput = function(e) {
          let value = e.target.value;
          if (!/^\d{1,2}?$/gi.test(value)) {
            e.target.value = value.substr(0, 2);
          }
        };
      }
    }
  }
`

### What is expected?
I hope I can only enter two digits.

### What is actually happening?
After entering the integer, switch the focus to another 'input' and enter the number, which will cause the original value to be modified.
For example: I enter 11 in the first "input", then immediately switch to the second Input input 22, and finally switch to the first "input" input 3 will appear 223. If you switch to the second input again and Enter 4 then the value of the first input will be changed to 2234

